{
  "texts": [
    "developed a webserver called PASSer (Prediction of Allosteric Sites Server) to predict allosteric sites in a given target.",
    "The webserver uses three ML models, (i) an ensemble learning model, (ii) an automated ML model, and (iii) a learning-to-rank model.",
    "PAS-Ser makes remarkably rapid predictions, typically providing allosteric site results within seconds (Tian et al. 2021).",
    "The ensemble learning method involved both an XGBoost model and a graph-based CNN.",
    "The physical properties of the protein pockets are fed into the former model, and its atomic representation is fed into the latter."
  ]
}